    • Method Detail

      • getCategories

        rx.Observable<GfycatCategoriesList> getCategories()
        Request categories list from cache. If none found - network request will be performed.

        If found in cache but expired - will return cached one and perform network request for updates

        Returns:
        GfycatCategoriesList observable.

      • getGfycats

        rx.Observable<FeedData> getGfycats(android.content.Context context,
                                   FeedIdentifier feedIdentifier)
        Request gfycats retrieval from cache. If no gfycats found - network request will be performed.

        Any further cache updates (caused by getMoreGfycats(FeedDescription feedDescription), refresh(FeedIdentifier feedIdentifier), etc.) will trigger onNext call.

        !!! Warning: You should NOT forget to unsubscribe otherwise memory leak will occur.

        Parameters:
        feedIdentifier - - to subscribe for.
        Returns:
        FeedData observable.

      • getNewGfycats

        rx.Observable<Void> getNewGfycats(FeedDescription feedDescription)
        Network request for new gfycats on top of .

        For now this works only with FeedDescription obtained with PublicFeedIdentifier.trending() used in getGfycats(Context, FeedIdentifier) observable.

        Parameters:
        feedDescription - from the latest FeedData that you get with getGfycats(Context, FeedIdentifier)
        Returns:
        Returns Observable calling onError in case of failure or onComplete in case of success.

      • getMoreGfycats

        rx.Observable<Void> getMoreGfycats(FeedDescription feedDescription)
        Request more gfycats for corresponding feed. Will download gfycats and save to local database if needed.

        Use getGfycats(Context context, FeedIdentifier feedIdentifier) observable to subscribe for these updates.

        Parameters:
        feedDescription - from latest FeedData that you get from getGfycats(Context, FeedIdentifier) for same feedIdentifier.
        Returns:
        Returns Observable calling onError in case of failure or onComplete in case of success

      • refresh

        void refresh(FeedIdentifier feedIdentifier)
        Drop cache and request new gfycats from network.
        Parameters:
        feedIdentifier - that should be dropped.

      • getGfycat

        rx.Observable<Gfycat> getGfycat(String gfyId)
        Looks for Gfycat in cache. Requests one from network if not found.
        Returns:
        Returns Observable emitting a single Gfycat object or null if not found neither in cache nor during network request.
